    static enum TimeHashUtils.SubSecond
extends java.lang.Enum<TimeHashUtils.SubSecond>
    Handles sub-seconds hashing and unhashing.
    Value Period Frequency Precision compared to previous value Number of characters including YMdHms
    TRIM 1 s 1 Hz   6
    MILLIGROUP 25 ms 40 Hz 40x 7
    MILLIS 1 ms 1 KHz 25x 8
    MICROGROUP 10 Î¼s 100 KHz 100x 9
    NANOGROUP 200 ns 5 MHz 50x 10
    QUADNANO 4 ns 250 MHz 50x 11
    NANOS 1 ns 1 GHz 4x 12

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      MICROGROUP
      Provides precision up to every 10 microseconds, for a 9-character string.
      Effectively 100 KHz, or 100x more precise than MILLIS.
      MILLIGROUP
      Provides precision up to every 25 milliseconds, for a 7-character string.
      Effectively 40 Hz, or 40x more precise than TRIM.
      MILLIS
      Provides milliseconds precision, for an 8-character string.
      25x more precise than MILLIGROUP.
      NANOGROUP
      Provides precision up to every 200 nanoseconds, for a 10-character string.
      50x more precise than MICROGROUP.
      NANOS
      Provides nanoseconds precision, for a 12-character string.
      4x more precise than QUADNANO.
      QUADNANO
      Provides precision up to every 4 nanoseconds, for an 11-character string.
      50x more precise than NANOGROUP.
      TRIM
      Trims sub-seconds, for a 6-character string.
